{{Quote|He is a pig! He is a savage! Do not believe a word he says.|King Frane|<ref name="TSP">''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Shattered Peace]]''</ref>}}
'''Swines''', also called '''pigs''', were quadrupedal [[Mammal/Legends|mammals]]. Their main physical characteristics, including their blunt-ended [[Nose/Legends|nose]], large size, and hooves, were archetypal of [[Porcine/Legends|porcine]] [[Species/Legends|species]].<ref name="NEGAS">''[[The New Essential Guide to Alien Species]]''</ref> To compare a person to a pig was an insult, at least amongst [[Rutanian]]s<ref name="TSP" /> and [[Calian]] [[Human/Legends|Humans]].<ref name="Starfire Rising">[[Star Wars (1977) 54|''Star Wars'' (1977) 54]]</ref> The expression "pearls before swine" referred to giving things of value to those who would not understand or appreciate it.<ref name="DFR">''[[Dark Force Rising]]''</ref> 

In addition, some sentient species such as the [[Ugnaught/Legends|Ugnaughts]] and [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorreans]] had physical similarities to pigs, namely the snout and, to a lesser extent, their vocal language. In the latter case, their similarities were to such an extent that Gamorrean guards have even been called pig guards due to the resemblance.

Rebel pilot [[Jek Tono Porkins/Legends|Jek Porkins]] was playfully nicknamed "Piggy" by his squad mates, who often teased him about his heavyset physique. Years after Porkins' death at the [[Battle of Yavin]], [[Wes Janson/Legends|Wes Janson]] and [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antillies]] told [[Wraith Squadron]]'s Gamorrean recruit [[Voort saBinring]], that they did not consider his nickname "Piggy" derogatory, but a legacy to live up to.<ref name="XW:WS">''[[X-Wing: Wraith Squadron]]''</ref>

